Package: dune-server
Version: 12.8.2
Section: games
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: powershell (>= 7.4), openssh-client, xdg-utils
Recommends: postgresql-client, jq, python3-gi, gir1.2-webkit2-4.1, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, libvirt-clients
Suggests: rabbitmq-server, libvirt-daemon-system, qemu-system-x86
Maintainer: Coastal <coastal-ms@users.noreply.github.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/coastal-ms/DST-DuneServerTool
Description: Self-hosted Dune: Awakening server management portal
 Dune Server Tool (DST) is a self-hosted management portal for the Dune:
 Awakening dedicated server. It runs a local PowerShell + Vite web UI on
 127.0.0.1 with a per-launch tokenized URL, served either in your browser or
 in a native GTK desktop window (the Recommends pull in WebKitGTK for that).
 .
 The PowerShell backend, web UI, and SSH/kubectl management come over from the
 Windows build and run under pwsh. Where Windows uses Hyper-V to host the
 server VM, the Linux build uses libvirt/KVM (install the Suggests), or you can
 point DST at an existing server over SSH (set ServerHost in dune-server.config)
 and skip local virtualization entirely.
 .
 See /opt/dune-server/LINUX-PORT-STATUS.md for the current state of the port.
